data.title: Is Kate Middleton receiving treatment in Houston? Kensington Palace maintains silence. The inside story
meta_keywords: Kate Middleton receiving treatment in Houston
data.meta_description: Kensington Palace has refused to share information on whether Kate Middleton has received treatment in Houston on the grounds of medical privacy.
data.text:
Synopsis

Kensington Palace has refused to share information on whether Kate Middleton has received treatment in Houston on the grounds of medical privacy.

What type of cancer Princess of Wales Kate Middleton has? This is the question that has been asked many times since the Royal Palace announced that the princess is suffering from a life-threatening disease. She as well as Kensington Palace has refused to divulge any information on this issue. But this question has become important after rumors began doing the rounds that Kate Middleton was possibly receiving treatment at MD Anderson Cancer Center in Houston. Kensington Palace has since denied it.

What did TikTok royal expert say?

According to 'She Knows', TikTok royal expert, Amanda Matta (@matta_of_fact) shared a Reddit thread claiming that Kate was in Houston and staying at The St. Regis. She wrote on her Reddit account, "Was visiting friends at the St. Regis this weekend and they had spoken of her being at the hotel. Has anyone else heard this? Assuming she would be here for treatment. Hoping for the best outcome for the family.”

Matta wrote further that Houston also happens to be the home of MD Anderson which is often called the world’s top cancer treatment center. She also claims in the Reddit post that she can say comfortably that she has heard things like this for the past two months now with people saying that they’ve seen Kate, they’ve seen Kate’s security at MD Anderson in Houston.

MD Anderson Cancer Center keeps mum

'She Knows' has also reported that a representative for MD Anderson Cancer Center said that he couldn’t comment on whether the royal is or is not a patient at the facility due to strict privacy laws.

Kensington Palace: Medical Privacy

On the other hand, the palace too has said bluntly that it will not be sharing any specific diagnosis. A spokesperson of Kensington Palace told 'Yahoo Entertainment', "We will not be sharing any further private medical information. The Princess has a right to medical privacy, as we all do."

FAQs:

What has Kensington Palace said on whether Kate Middleton has received treatment in Houston?

Kensington Palace has refused to share information on whether Kate Middleton has received treatment in Houston on the grounds of medical privacy. A spokesperson said that the Princess has a right to medical privacy.

Who is Amanda Matta and what has she said about Kate Middleton's treatment?

Amanda Matta is a TikTok royal expert. She has said that she has information that Kate Middleton has been staying in Houston and her security staff has been seen at MD Anderson Cancer Center.
